17:58.860 --> 18:05.940
Haldeman has been involved in two multi-book series, one called Atar the Merman, and the other was Star Trek from the TV series.

18:06.440 --> 18:12.180
Although he enjoyed writing the first of his three Atar books, the ones that followed had nowhere to go to expand the characters.

18:12.900 --> 18:20.100
The publisher was banking on the current popularity of dolphins and whales, but the series never took hold and Haldeman's third book was never published.

18:20.100 --> 18:23.940
The Star Trek novels were a different sort of challenge, as Haldeman explains.

18:51.380 --> 18:51.820
Haldeman had to work out some other problems first.

18:52.060 --> 18:57.180
He was asked whether anybody was picking up Jim's work, and he said, why don't you give it a try.

18:57.700 --> 19:06.940
Jim was taking the scripts from the TV show and just turning them into short stories, whereas they wanted me to do what Jim would have done if he had lived,

19:07.120 --> 19:11.120
which was write original novels around the Star Trek characters.

19:12.640 --> 19:17.400
Writing these novels was more than just sitting down and coming up with something for Spock, McCoy, and Kirk to do.

19:17.840 --> 19:20.020
Haldeman had to work out some other problems first.

20:00.000 --> 20:05.800
One of Haldeman's latest projects is a trilogy, of which the first book, Worlds, is already out.

20:06.040 --> 20:08.160
Haldeman gave us a little background on that novel.

20:17.400 --> 20:20.900
It was born and grew up on a space colony, a space settlement.

20:21.680 --> 20:27.760
It is sent to Earth for a year of postgraduate work or finishing, if you want to call it that.

20:28.440 --> 20:38.060
Being set up for a political position as a liaison between this world and Earth, and various strange things happened to her in the year that she's here.

20:38.060 --> 20:44.120
It's sort of an old Yeldon Suramann kind of a novel.

20:45.000 --> 20:49.320
She grows by being sort of bounced around by Earth.

20:51.220 --> 20:59.680
And the second novel, Stars, takes over for the first one in and takes her into all age.

21:01.500 --> 21:06.820
It seems as if a lot of authors are writing trilogies these days, and we wondered why Haldeman decided to write one.

21:09.180 --> 21:13.560
Well, it seems like an awfully big thing to put into one book.

21:15.040 --> 21:23.480
And it looks as if each one of the trilogy, each volume of the trilogy will be longer than any other book that was written by us.

21:23.480 --> 21:30.840
At least a third, if you want so indeed, it would have been a book nearly a half million words long.

21:31.420 --> 21:32.980
So, right, they're difficult to sell.

21:35.000 --> 21:40.680
And I just, you know, everybody's doing trilogies, so I can't I do a trilogy too, it's part of it.

21:41.440 --> 21:43.880
They're very successful.

21:44.820 --> 21:47.980
The second and third books have a built-in audience.

21:51.080 --> 21:52.800
Also, I wanted to try something big.

21:54.420 --> 21:56.000
And that's as good a reason as any.

21:56.420 --> 22:00.680
We've discussed in the previous sections of this interview that Haldeman's main concern is storytelling.

22:01.420 --> 22:05.540
He develops interesting characters and sets them in a believable scientific background.

